text: Phoebe chekiangensis is a species of tree up to in the family Lauraceae. It is endemic to China where it occurs in Fujian, Jiangxi, and Zhejiang provinces. Its name refers to Zhejiang province that is written "Chekiang" in Wade–Giles romanization. It is threatened by habitat loss. It is under second-class national protection in China. ==References== Category:Endemic flora of China Category:Trees of China chekiangensis Category:Vulnerable plants Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
